CSS means Cascading Style Sheets
Not a programming language
used alongside HTML, used for website layout and design.
Able to extend the functionality of CSS with Sass/Less

3 methods for adding CSS
    Inline CSS: Directly in the HTML element. (Don't do this)
    Internal CSS: Using <Style> tages within a single document.
    External CSS: Linking an External .css file. 

Colors in CSS:
    Color Names
    HTML5 Color Names
    Hexadecimal
    RGB
Example:
    body{
        Color: red;
        background: coral
    }
    h1{
        color: #00ff00;
    }
    p{
        color: rgb(0,0,255)
    }
